---
source: crates/normalize/tests/cli_snapshots.rs
expression: "snapshot_help(&[])"
---
normalize - Structural code intelligence: index symbols and calls, enforce rules, track complexity.

Usage: normalize [OPTIONS] [COMMAND]

Commands:
  grep       Find code by text pattern. Use when you know what the code looks like but not where it is.
  aliases    List filter aliases. Use to see available shorthand names for --exclude/--only globs.
  context    Inject project context into LLM prompts. Use to provide per-project instructions to agents.
  init       Set up normalize in a new project. Run once after cloning to create .normalize/ config.
  update     Check for and install newer versions of normalize.
  translate  Convert code between programming languages. Use for porting or understanding unfamiliar syntax.
  ci         Run all quality checks in one pass. Use in CI pipelines or before committing to catch violations.
  view       Browse code structure and symbol relationships. Use to read files, explore types, or trace dependencies.
  daemon     Control the background daemon that keeps the index fresh automatically.
  grammars   Install and list tree-sitter grammars. Run after install or when parsing fails for a language.
  guide      Step-by-step workflow guides. Use when learning normalize or onboarding a new codebase.
  generate   Generate code from an API spec. Use to scaffold clients or types from OpenAPI definitions.
  structure  Build and query the code index. Run `structure rebuild` after cloning or when cross-file commands return stale results.
  syntax     Inspect parsed syntax trees and test queries. Use to debug grammars or develop tree-sitter patterns.
  package    Query package metadata and dependencies. Use to check versions, find outdated deps, or view dep trees.
  sessions   Review AI agent session logs. Use to check cost, duration, and tool usage across coding sessions.
  tools      Run linters, formatters, and test runners. Unified interface to external ecosystem tools.
  edit       Edit code by symbol name. Use for batch renames, signature changes, or pattern-based rewrites.
  analyze    Assess codebase quality. Use for health checks, finding duplicates, security scanning, and architecture analysis.
  rank       Rank files and functions by metrics. Use to find the most complex, longest, or most coupled code.
  trend      Plot metrics over git history. Use to see if complexity, size, or test coverage is trending up or down.
  budget     Enforce diff budgets on PRs. Use to cap how much complexity or size can grow per change.
  ratchet    Prevent metric regressions. Records a baseline and fails CI if metrics get worse.
  rules      Configure and run lint rules. Use to enable/disable checks or see what rules are available.
  config     Inspect and validate .normalize/config.toml. Use to debug config issues or see available options.
  serve      Start a normalize server. Use to expose normalize over MCP, HTTP, or LSP for editor integration.
  help       Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --pretty                     Human-friendly output with colors and formatting
      --compact                    Compact output without colors (overrides TTY detection)
      --jsonl                      Output one JSON object per line (for arrays)
      --json                       Output machine-readable JSON
      --jq <jq>                    Filter output through jq expression
      --input-schema               Print JSON Schema of the subcommand's input parameters and exit
      --output-schema              Print JSON Schema of the subcommand's return type and exit
      --params-json <params-json>  Provide all parameters as a JSON object instead of individual flags
  -h, --help                       Print help
  -V, --version                    Print version
